rates that renowned figures such as Leonora Carrington, Maya Deren, Alejandro Jodorowsky and Jan Švankmajer took part in shaping a vibrant and distinctive surrealist film culture following the Second World War. Addressing highly influential films and directors related to international surrealism during the second half of the twentieth century, it expands the purview of both surrealism and film studies by situating surrealism as a major force in postwar cinema.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picturesxHistoryy20th century. 0aSurrealism in motion pictures. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2021. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAlejandro Jodorowsky.  aAndré Breton.  aCinema.  aFilm.  aJan Švankmajer.  aJoseph Cornell.  aLuis Buñuel.  aMaya Deren.  aPost-war.  aSurrealism.1 aBolt Rasmussen, Mikkel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFijałkowski, Krzysztof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGee, Felicity, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGunning, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammond, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLöwy, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaillet, Arnaud, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoheden, Kristoffer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNoheden, Kristoffer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aParkinson, Gavin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRichardson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSusik, Abigail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/voc